---
description: Factor orthogonalization workflow for Cursor agents
globs:
alwaysApply: false
---

When the user asks to neutralize, orthogonalize, residualize, remove style exposure, remove industry exposure, or reduce correlation to existing factors, follow `SKILL.md`.

Key requirements:

- Use only T-date available controls.
- Run daily cross-sectional regression, not pooled regression.
- Report exposure before/after and signal quality before/after.
- Re-evaluate the residual factor with the project's factor evaluation workflow.
- Never use forward returns, labels, or test-period statistics as controls.
